# Deno Web Standards App

A simple Todo application built with Deno 2 and Action Web Components, demonstrating a standards-first approach to web development.

## Features

- Server-side rendering with Deno
- Action Web Components for dynamic UI updates
- No frontend framework - uses vanilla JavaScript and web standards
- Progressive enhancement approach

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Deno 2.0+](https://deno.com/) installed on your machine

### Running the Application

1. Clone this repository
2. Navigate to the project directory
3. Run the development server:

```bash
deno task dev
```

4. Open your browser and visit http://localhost:8000

## Project Structure

- `server.ts` - Main Deno server file
- `/static` - Static assets (JS, CSS)
  - `/js/action-components.js` - Action Web Components definitions
- `/views` - Server-side view templates
- `/routes` - Route handlers

## Action Web Components

This project uses Action Web Components (AWC) for server-driven UI updates:

- `<ac-yellow-fade>` - Applies a yellow highlight effect to an element
- `<ac-toggle-class>` - Toggles a CSS class on an element
- `<ac-children>` - Replaces the children of an element

